		<ul>
			<li>Deep Freeze Standard: $40 x 5 = $200 one-time</li>
			<li>Network-level DNS filtering: Free (OpenDNS) or $60/year (CleanBrowsing)</li>
			<li>Antivirus (Windows Defender built-in): Free</li>
			<li>Annual maintenance: ~$300/year</li>
			<li><strong>Total Year 1:</strong> $500-600</li>
			<li><strong>Annual ongoing:</strong> $300-400</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Medium Lab (15 Computers) - Professional Setup</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Windows Server + CALs: $1,500 one-time</li>
			<li>Server hardware: $2,000 one-time</li>
			<li>Workstation filtering software: $30/computer/year x 15 = $450/year</li>
			<li>Deep Freeze (optional): $40 x 15 = $600 one-time</li>
			<li>IT consultant for setup: $1,500 one-time</li>
			<li><strong>Total Year 1:</strong> $6,050</li>
			<li><strong>Annual ongoing:</strong> $450-800/year</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Budget Tips</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Consider refurbished computers ($200-400 vs $800+ new)</li>
			<li>Negotiate volume discounts on software</li>
			<li>Check for nonprofit/education pricing</li>
			<li>Use free/open-source solutions where appropriate</li>
			<li>Plan replacement cycle (5-7 years per computer)</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

